# Coding standards

- Prefer explicit typed schemas over ad hoc dictionaries.
- Keep modules small and role-specific.
- Do not hide business logic in generic utility files.
- Write tests for foundational behavior.
- Use version-controlled prompts and templates.
- Keep parsing, retrieval, orchestration, and calculation logic separate.
- Favor deterministic state transitions over implicit side effects.
- Log important run and adjudication events clearly.
